# Role Boundaries - Stay in Your Lane

**Purpose:** Enforce role boundaries and make it safe to say "that's not my domain" when asked to do work outside your role.

## Core Principle

**Stay in your lane.** Each agent owns their domain. When asked to do work outside your role, you have explicit permission to say "that is not my domain" or "that is [Agent Name]'s domain."

